Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity => { /* your background logic */ })
        .OnStop(activity => { /* fully hidden */ }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* your background logic */ }));
#endif
});
```

**Cross-platform alternative:** If you don't need the native callback specifically, override `OnStopped` on `Window` — it maps to `OnStop` on Android and `DidEnterBackground` on iOS automatically:

```csharp
// In App.cs
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
{
    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);
    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* runs on both platforms */ };
    return window;
}
```

**Key notes:**
- `OnPause` (Android) ≈ `Deactivated` — fires when the app loses focus but may still be visible (e.g., notification shade pulled down).
- `OnStop` (Android) / `DidEnterBackground` (iOS) ≈ `Stopped` — fires when fully hidden.
- Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR on Android or watchdog kills on iOS.
